{"TopicId":186689,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Flying in first person","CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-25T01:06:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-25T01:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(as always i usually post the wrong topic in the wrong forum so an admin is more than welcome to move this)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just reached orbit in one of my SSTOs in first person only (which also mean no maneuver nodes, it was actually really fun). It was basically instrument flying and i realized how usefully the physical instruments in the cockpit are. After you leave the atmosphere they don\u0027t seem to do that much since I guess they assume it\u0027s only for kerbin flight but yeah, I\u0027m always impressed with this game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loskene","CreatedById":141778,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-25T01:13:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want useful IVA instruments in space you need to install RasterPropMonitor. I would like more reasons for IVA flight in the stock game though, it\u0027s a very different experience.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-25T01:28:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223640554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564017208\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022141778\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loskene\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Loskene said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want useful IVA instruments in space you need to install RasterPropMonitor. I would like more reasons for IVA flight in the stock game though, it\u0027s a very different experience.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni try not to use toooo many mods except kerbal engineer, but the official update actually included some of those readouts so it\u0027s much easier, still i just like having it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-25T01:48:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s the video btw \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/HU0fAlEnrMo?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-26T12:41:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, rendezvous and dock in IVA!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flavio hc16","CreatedById":183153,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-26T12:54:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223641256\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564144877\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114432\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mahnarch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Mahnarch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, rendezvous and dock in IVA!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did a lot of docking in 1st person with mk1-2-3 Pos and i can tell you that the are extremely satisfying\u00A0 to pull off\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-26T16:13:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would tend to think that a truly immersive IVA experience might\u00A0also include some VR options.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s\u00A0beyond my ancient technical capabilities to even discuss architectural\u00A0details of\u00A0it, but from a user perspective it could (if well executed)\u00A0be a very cool\u00A0experience.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MR L A","CreatedById":150940,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-26T23:40:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223641351\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564157608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297357\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wallygator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Wallygator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would tend to think that a truly immersive IVA experience might\u00A0also include some VR options.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u2019s\u00A0beyond my ancient technical capabilities to even discuss architectural\u00A0details of\u00A0it, but from a user perspective it could (if well executed)\u00A0be a very cool\u00A0experience.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree, but probably a bit too intensive to slap on the already-cpu-intensive-KSP \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T18:30:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223641598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564184420\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150940\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MR L A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/27/2019 at 12:40 AM, MR L A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree, but probably a bit too intensive to slap on the already-cpu-intensive-KSP \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh\u00A0well, guess it\u0027s back to \u0022one eye only\u0022\u00A0for\u00A0the performance boost!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GKSP","CreatedById":160883,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T20:02:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do have a question about the instruments.\u00A0 What\u0027s the one that has the three hands that always slowly rotate, and looks kinda like a clock numbered from 0 to 9 or so?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T20:19:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223642463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564344148\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GKSP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, GKSP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do have a question about the instruments.\u00A0 What\u0027s the one that has the three hands that always slowly rotate, and looks kinda like a clock numbered from 0 to 9 or so?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe that\u2019s an altimeter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T21:53:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy limited experience with IVA piloting has been, to quote Mr. Indiana Jones:\u00A0 \u003Cem\u003EFly, yes.\u00A0 Land, no.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-30T23:27:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223642521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564350786\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165625\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aegolius13\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/28/2019 at 4:53 PM, Aegolius13 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy limited experience with IVA piloting has been, to quote Mr. Indiana Jones:\u00A0 \u003Cem\u003EFly, yes.\u00A0 Land, no.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat nightflying (instrument flying) has taught me was try to keep the\u00A0 prograde marker right at or just above the middle line until you touch down \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chryssalid 8492","CreatedById":197332,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-31T00:52:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223642521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564350786\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165625\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aegolius13\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/28/2019 at 5:53 PM, Aegolius13 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy limited experience with IVA piloting has been, to quote Mr. Indiana Jones:\u00A0 \u003Cem\u003EFly, yes.\u00A0 Land, no.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add onto \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194521-reinhart-mk1/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022194521\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194521-reinhart-mk1/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Reinhart Mk.1\u003C/a\u003E \u0027s if you haven\u0027t done so already stick a flag or \u003Ca href=\u0022https://1drv.ms/u/s!Aoo6szyB84IXgTdjyoq-cFI7bzbM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esomething\u003C/a\u003E at the end of the runway that can be targeted and use it as an ILS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reinhart Mk.1","CreatedById":194521,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-31T00:55:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223643582\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564534332\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Chryssalid 8492\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Chryssalid 8492 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add onto \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194521-reinhart-mk1/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022194521\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194521-reinhart-mk1/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Reinhart Mk.1\u003C/a\u003E \u0027s if you haven\u0027t done so already stick a flag or \u003Ca href=\u0022https://1drv.ms/u/s!Aoo6szyB84IXgTdjyoq-cFI7bzbM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esomething\u003C/a\u003E at the end of the runway that can be targeted and use it as an ILS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis guy gets it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-07-31T00:56:15Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2019 12:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Reinhart Mk.1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Servo","CreatedById":149419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-31T01:04:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had some fun with IVA flying at the helm of the rare non-replica craft that I build in a while.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227OLbMtR.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/7OLbMtR.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe loadout for \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toss_bombing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Etoss bombing\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0against the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. SOP is to drop the bombs in pairs in a 200m/s climb 5km away from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E to increase probability of hitting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022E2I1LSU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/E2I1LSU.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe result of a spectacular direct hit against the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E - the flight profile on this one was to fly in high, dive down, then pitch up quickly in a loop, dropping the bombs at about alpha = 30 and 3km range. I was greeted by this view after I completed the loop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis flight was flow entirely within IVA, including a successful landing (off the runway. You can\u0027t have everything)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"T-Bouw","CreatedById":21500,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-01T13:37:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223643535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564529279\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Reinhart Mk.1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/31/2019 at 1:27 AM, Reinhart Mk.1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat nightflying (instrument flying) has taught me was try to keep the\u00A0 prograde marker right at or just above the middle line until you touch down \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might be better served in the long run to use the \u0022rate of ascent/descent indicator\u0022 to the right of the altimeter. Just keep the hand between 0 and -5 for a smooth landing.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlmost every plane has a different \u0022angle of attack\u0022 to fly level or make a landing. The throttle is even more of a factor in this, as you may already know, a lower setting needs a higher angle of attack. But using the rate indicator is always reliable.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe fun and challenge of flying in IVA is certainly undeniable!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-01T13:38:53Z\u0022 title=\u002208/01/2019 01:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 1, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by T-Bouw\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eextra info!\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}